gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

Did Tilak adorn Chandan, Re; Sat down yourself on that very seat, Re;
Kept steady gaze, Unwavering, Re; Within your own Self, Endless, Re.

Here is the translation:

My own attention is engaged by myself, my own soul's understanding is revealed; 
Many Gopal and Andal are beside me, with Shukmuni as my eternal friend.

Here is the translation:

With my own people, I walk with them, not found in my own way; 
In the sky, an immortal one comes, having sung the praise, it is to be made.

Here is the translation:

The auspicious day of Chaitra, the eighth day, is celebrated; 
Then Ganesha is worshipped by Gopala, keeping sorrow from body and mind away.

Here is the translation:

Flower garland on the chest worn are, then that person is considered done are; 
Say with hands tied so it is said, Why did you do it Lord, You made it why are.

Here is the translation:

One makes the noise in the meeting of Arati, that which calls is taking along; 
The story gets heard in the gathering, and the clear proof comes to know.
